.IX Title "probes::Curl 3"
.TH probes::Curl 3 "2005-01-15" "1.38" "SmokePing"
.SH "NAME"
probes::Curl \- a curl(1) probe for SmokePing
.SH "OVERVIEW"
.IX Header "OVERVIEW"
Fetches an \s-1HTTP\s0 or \s-1HTTPS\s0 \s-1URL\s0 using \fIcurl\fR\|(1).
.SH "SYNOPSYS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSYS"
.Vb 2
\& *** Probes ***
\& + Curl
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 1
\& binary = /usr/bin/curl # default value
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 1
\& *** Targets ***
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 2
\& probe = Curl
\& forks = 10
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 3
\& menu = Top
\& title = Top Menu
\& remark = Top Menu Remark
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 1
\& + PROBE_CONF
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 4
\& + First
\& menu = First
\& title = First Target
\& host = some.host
.Ve
.PP
.Vb 4
\& # PROBE_CONF can be overridden here
\& ++ PROBE_CONF
\& agent = "User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.2.1) Gecko/20021130"
\& url = https://some.host/some/where
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Supported probe-specific variables:
.IP "binary" 4
.IX Item "binary"
The location of your curl binary.
.IP "forks" 4
.IX Item "forks"
The number of concurrent processes to be run. See \fIprobes::basefork\fR\|(3pm)
for details.
.IP "url" 4
.IX Item "url"
The \s-1URL\s0 to fetch.  Can be any one that curl supports.
.PP
Supported target-level probe variables 
(see \fIcurl\fR\|(1) for details of the options):
.IP "agent" 4
.IX Item "agent"
The \*(L"\-A\*(R" \fIcurl\fR\|(1) option.  This is a full \s-1HTTP\s0 User-Agent header including
the words \*(L"User\-Agent:\*(R".  It should be enclosed in quotes if it contains
shell metacharacters
.IP "ssl2" 4
.IX Item "ssl2"
The \*(L"\-2\*(R" \fIcurl\fR\|(1) option.  Force \s-1SSL2\s0.
.IP "timeout" 4
.IX Item "timeout"
The \*(L"\-m\*(R" \fIcurl\fR\|(1) option.  Maximum timeout in seconds.
.IP "interface" 4
.IX Item "interface"
The \*(L"\-\-interface\*(R" \fIcurl\fR\|(1) option.  Bind to a specific interface, \s-1IP\s0 address or
host name.
